  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Principal Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>Manufacture of dies, moulds, tools, jigs and fixtures.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will lead CNC milling programming and machine operation to produce precision parts according to specifications, driving process improvements that enhance productivity, quality, and cost efficiency.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Program CNC milling machines Hwacheon, MAZAK, and Faunc using Master Cam, NX, and AutoCad to produce parts that meet drawing specifications</li><li>Operate and set up CNC machines independently to ensure accurate production of parts</li><li>Apply knowledge of machine tools, speeds, feeds, and insert technology to optimize machining processes</li><li>Perform 3D/CNC programming and set up turn-mill machines to support manufacturing requirements</li><li>Provide technical support for production issues, including designing and redesigning jigs and fixtures to improve machining efficiency</li><li>Plan and implement machining process improvements to shorten cycle times, increase productivity, enhance quality, reduce waste, and control costs</li><li>Verify finished parts conform to specifications using appropriate measuring and inspection tools</li><li>Schedule and deploy daily work assignments to meet production targets</li><li>Communicate effectively with team members to determine and refine process procedures</li><li>Train colleagues on CNC programming and machine operation techniques as needed</li><li>Execute assigned ad-hoc duties with diligence and responsibility</li></ul>",
